JOHANNESBURG - The public has until the end of February to make written submissions on amending Section 25 of the Constitution. The amendment will allow land expropriation without compensation. READ: Land reform department launches new website During an interview with eNCA, the chairperson of Parliament's Ad Hoc Committee on Section 25, Mathole Motshekga said depending on the comments they receive, they will make a decision that may include extending the deadline for written submissions. Later that day, the committee announced a unanimous consensus had been reached that the deadline for written submissions on the draft amendment to Section 25 of the Constitution is extended to the 28 February 2020. This amendment gives effect to land expropriation without compensation.